<p>Madagascar’s presidency says an attempted illegal seizure of power is underway after elements of the military joined youth-led anti-government protests that have stretched for weeks [csmonitor.com#1][straitstimes.com#3][allafrica.com#7]. A mutinied army unit declared it had taken control of the country’s armed forces and the leadership of the military command, a claim reported by local and international media [bbc.com#5][allafrica.com#6]. The announcement came a day after soldiers, including members of an elite unit, aligned themselves with demonstrators calling for political change [abcnews.go.com#2][japantoday.com#4]. The Associated Press also reported exchanges of gunfire between the mutinous group and pro-government security forces as they demanded President Andry Rajoelina step down [apnews.com#8].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/SbOxhbzFZzAjfryNDdtT6XbO56VZa0WErUQ-yh5X2K7rTx2QflkeeXD_nbZKID-_0aA6IjNt0fbLuMxUex0hQ6O38CVRBDhsRr2Dzdb1cnK-TMmI9a1-dLDHm_6P8oM1L4Z-Sc5y61vsYWk89vZ002ytYK5-TIHc1Y6MopipNg' alt='Anti-government demonstrations in Madagascar as some soldiers join protests.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Presidency stance: The presidency described events as an “attempt to seize power illegally,” without offering details [csmonitor.com#1][allafrica.com#7].</li><li>Mutiny claim: A mutinied army unit declared it had taken over the armed forces and military command [bbc.com#5][allafrica.com#6].</li><li>Protest backdrop: Soldiers joined youth-led demonstrations that have lasted more than two weeks [abcnews.go.com#2][straitstimes.com#3].</li><li>Elite unit role: Members of an elite army unit were among those who sided with protesters [japantoday.com#4][abcnews.go.com#2].</li><li>Clashes reported: AP reported gunfire exchanges between mutineers and pro-government security forces amid demands for the president’s resignation [apnews.com#8].</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Madagascar presidency: Framed the turmoil as an “attempted illegal and forcible seizure of power,” while providing no further details. (<a href='https://allafrica.com/stories/202510120065.html'>AllAfrica (New Times)</a>)</li><li>Mutinied army unit: Declared it was taking control of all military forces and the leadership of the military command. (<a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cd070pn4g07o'>BBC News</a>)</li><li>Protesting soldiers and demonstrators: Demanded President Andry Rajoelina step down amid exchanges of gunfire with pro-government security forces. (<a href='https://apnews.com/article/madagascar-protests-attempted-coup-e6dd29a429e06362efd238cfac7270d0'>AP News</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.csmonitor.com/World/Africa/2025/1012/madascar-president-alleges-coup-protests'>Madagascar’s president says an attempted coup is in progress</a> - csmonitor.com</li><li><a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/madagascars-president-coup-underway-after-soldiers-joined-anti-126445257'>Madagascar&#x27;s president says a coup is underway after soldiers joined anti-government demonstrations</a> - abcnews.go.com</li><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/Madagascar-president-warns-of-coup-attempt-as-more-soldiers-join-protests'>Madagascar president warns of coup attempt as more soldiers join protests</a> - straitstimes.com</li><li><a href='https://japantoday.com/category/world/an-attempted-coup-is-underway-in-madagascar-the-country%27s-president-says'>Madagascar&#x27;s president says coup underway after soldiers join anti-government demonstrations</a> - japantoday.com</li><li><a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cd070pn4g07o'>Madagascar presidency says attempt to seize power under way</a> - bbc.com</li><li><a href='https://allafrica.com/stories/202510130014.html'>Madagascar: Madagascar President Says Illegal Power Grab Underway After Army Mutiny</a> - allafrica.com</li><li><a href='https://apnews.com/article/madagascar-protests-attempted-coup-e6dd29a429e06362efd238cfac7270d0'>Mal